body:
@tcNickolas thanks! I've fixed the code and squashed the last commits. Regarding the code style:
1. I think we need blank lines to improve readability. e.g. I sometimes add blank lines to separate final member variables from the mutable ones, or use them between logical blocks of code - say, to separate logging from main logic, and so on. I think we can be a bit creative here as long as checkstyle does not complain.
2. I agree that `this.` prefix is often redundant. We use that style from the beginning of the project because it was in some coding guidelines that we had followed then (or was it some default IDE setting?) Anyway, we are stuck with it now, so I use it to be consistent with the rest of the code. I absolutely don't mind if someone would offer a PR that converts all code to `this`-less style.
